.SH NAME
Protocol::WebSocket::Client \- WebSocket client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    my $sock = ...get non\-blocking socket...;
\&
\&    my $client = Protocol::WebSocket\->new(url => \*(Aqws://localhost:3000\*(Aq);
\&    $client\->on(
\&        write => sub {
\&            my $client = shift;
\&            my ($buf) = @_;
\&
\&            syswrite $sock, $buf;
\&        }
\&    );
\&    $client\->on(
\&        read => sub {
\&            my $client = shift;
\&            my ($buf) = @_;
\&
\&            ...do smth with read data...
\&        }
\&    );
\&
\&    # Sends a correct handshake header
\&    $client\->connect;
\&
\&    # Register on connect handler
\&    $client\->on(
\&        connect => sub {
\&            $client\->write(\*(Aqhi there\*(Aq);
\&        }
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parses incoming data and on every frame calls on_read
\&    $client\->read(...data from socket...);
\&
\&    # Sends correct close header
\&    $client\->disconnect;
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Protocol::WebSocket::Client is a convenient class for writing a WebSocket
client.
